# 🐞 bug report

### Affected Package
<!-- Can you pin-point one or more @angular/* packages as the source of the bug? -->
<!-- ✍️edit: --> The issue is caused by package @angular/core


### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
<!-- ✍️--> No, the previous version has the same behavior

### Description
There is an input on the page with using property binding to its value.

<b>html</b>
```HTML
<button (click)="onClick()">Set value</button>
<input type="text" [value]="getValue()">
```

A new value is set by clicking on the button as shown below

<b>ts</b>
```JavaScript
data = 'default value';
getValue() {
  return this.data;
}
 onClick() {
  this.data = 'new value';
}
```

The input at the first render has a value ```default value```. Then, after the first click on the button, it has the ```new value```.
If clear the value manually (select the value and remove it) and click on the button again, the value isn't updated.

I found a reason of this in source code ```core/src/render3/bindings.ts```

```JavaScript
export function bindingUpdated(lView: LView, bindingIndex: number, value: any): boolean {
  const oldValue = lView[bindingIndex];

  if (Object.is(oldValue, value)) {
    return false;
  } else {
    lView[bindingIndex] = value;
    return true;
  }
}
```

Because of the value isn't changed and the function has the ```Object.is(oldValue, value)``` condition, the input element doesn't update its value

is it expected behavior and is there some workaround to solve my problem?

P.S. The same problem exists if we update ```checked``` for radio/checkbox components

